WEBVTT

00:03.137 --> 00:04.172
All right, I've called you all
here to ask for your support.

00:04.205 --> 00:06.107
Taylor, my girlfriend --
We know Taylor.

00:06.140 --> 00:08.209
You don't have to specify
that she's your girlfriend

00:08.242 --> 00:10.311
every time.
I actually thought
her full name

00:10.344 --> 00:12.113
was "Taylormygirlfriend."
Now, wh--

00:12.146 --> 00:13.781
I don't always say it!

00:13.814 --> 00:16.016
Now, if I can
please continue...

00:16.050 --> 00:17.418
Taylor --

00:17.451 --> 00:19.187
[ Softly ]
my girlfriend --

00:19.220 --> 00:20.788
[ Sighs ]
[ Normal voice ]
...will be coming over today

00:20.821 --> 00:23.124
to celebrate
our 100 day-th anniversary.

00:23.157 --> 00:24.325
That's not a thing.

00:24.358 --> 00:25.659
And if it were,
100 "day-th"

00:25.693 --> 00:27.228
is not how you'd say it.

00:27.261 --> 00:29.863
"In a lot of movies,

00:29.897 --> 00:34.135
the pretty girl dates the dork
for a bet.

00:34.168 --> 00:37.371
I still think
this...is that."

00:37.405 --> 00:40.808
Good. This happens to be
exactly why I wanted to talk.

00:40.841 --> 00:42.810
I want you to get this all out
before she gets here.

00:42.843 --> 00:44.512
Insults,
embarrassing stories --

00:44.545 --> 00:46.947
Let's do this! The time that cat
chased Ray down the sewer.

00:46.980 --> 00:48.849
Remember when he ran into
the glass sliding door

00:48.882 --> 00:50.184
three times
at the same pool party?

00:50.218 --> 00:52.086
Bonk! Bonk! Bonk!

00:52.120 --> 00:54.222
Or the time he moonwalked
at the sixth-grade talent show.

00:54.255 --> 00:56.657
Yeah, it looked like
a horse was counting.

00:56.690 --> 00:58.025
[ Grunting, snorting ]

00:58.058 --> 00:59.693
You weren't even there
for that.
[ Laughter ]

00:59.727 --> 01:01.729
Yeah, well, I wasn't there
when they shot Lincoln, either.

01:01.762 --> 01:04.165
But a thing's bad enough,
word gets around.

01:04.198 --> 01:06.967
[ Laughter ]
Come on. You guys can do better
than that.

01:07.000 --> 01:09.069
What about all the cringy puns
with my name --

01:09.103 --> 01:10.804
my "Ray-cation"

01:10.838 --> 01:13.541
or when I threw myself
a "Ray-pride" parade?

01:13.574 --> 01:15.643
Or the multiple times
I was catfished?

01:15.676 --> 01:16.977
How about
my see-saw accident

01:17.010 --> 01:18.246
that "America's
Funniest Home Videos"

01:18.279 --> 01:20.181
deemed too crotch-violent
to air?

01:20.214 --> 01:21.715
My high-heel experiment?

01:25.886 --> 01:27.054
Taylor.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.690
I knocked,
but no one answered.

01:29.723 --> 01:31.525
Um...

01:31.559 --> 01:33.060
I don't know
if I want to do this

01:33.093 --> 01:35.763
in front of everyone,
but...

01:35.796 --> 01:38.532
Happy 100 Day-th
Anniversa-Ray!

01:38.566 --> 01:40.568
What?!
[ Chuckles ]

01:44.538 --> 01:47.241
Wow. There really is
someone for everyone.

01:47.275 --> 01:50.978
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:51.011 --> 01:52.380
[ Laughter ]

01:52.413 --> 01:54.047
Maya: Listen, Doctor,

01:54.081 --> 01:56.384
my friend's son has an untreated
stone fruit allergy.

01:56.417 --> 01:58.619
You'll see him this week,
or I'll have 15 moms

01:58.652 --> 02:00.554
come to your office
and hurl peaches at you.

02:01.789 --> 02:04.425
Friday at 2:00.
Yeah, thank you so much.

02:04.458 --> 02:05.693
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Where's Jimmy?

02:05.726 --> 02:07.928
Well, he came home from work
and collapsed.

02:07.961 --> 02:10.298
This promotion's
really taking it out of him.

02:10.331 --> 02:12.466
I hope you know
how silly you sound, Kenneth,

02:12.500 --> 02:15.269
'cause I am thriving.

02:15.303 --> 02:17.705
What? I let you keep
the fancy one.

02:17.738 --> 02:19.072
Jimmy, why are you
so bloody tired?

02:19.106 --> 02:20.941
Yeah, isn't the whole point
of being the boss

02:20.974 --> 02:22.776
so you can make
other people tired?

02:22.810 --> 02:24.512
Yeah, but I've been working
with these guys

02:24.545 --> 02:25.779
for a really long time.

02:25.813 --> 02:27.415
And by "working,"
I mean...

02:29.483 --> 02:31.752
Can someone make air quotes
for me?

02:31.785 --> 02:33.153
..."working."

02:33.187 --> 02:35.489
I find it weird to suddenly be
ordering them around.

02:35.523 --> 02:37.090
But I'm managing.

02:37.124 --> 02:39.893
Enh. Eh, eh. Ehh...

02:39.927 --> 02:40.994
[ Cellphone rings ]

02:41.028 --> 02:42.330
Hello?
[ Groans ]

02:42.363 --> 02:45.666
Stand down, Greer.
I got you the appointment.

02:45.699 --> 02:47.501
Is there nothing this
special-needs-mom phone tree

02:47.535 --> 02:48.802
cannot do?

02:48.836 --> 02:50.304
Right.
And you won't be needing

02:50.338 --> 02:52.139
all those peaches
after all.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.575
Oh, you did?

02:54.608 --> 02:56.310
I don't know.
Maybe a cobbler?

02:58.145 --> 03:00.614
My mom's always helping her
special-needs-mom friends, too.

03:00.648 --> 03:03.584
Yep, that's my mom --
always a helper, no downside.

03:03.617 --> 03:04.918
I just love how
we're so in syn--

03:04.952 --> 03:06.287
In sync!

03:06.320 --> 03:08.456
Whoa.
That was crazy.

03:08.489 --> 03:11.024
It's amazing how alike
our families are,

03:11.058 --> 03:13.361
how we're both so devoted
to our brothers.

03:14.995 --> 03:17.164
There he is --
the light of my life.

03:17.197 --> 03:19.667
All right, bring it in.
Come on.

03:21.569 --> 03:24.605
Ow! You jerk!
That kills!

03:24.638 --> 03:26.707
Ray!
That's your brother!

03:26.740 --> 03:28.909
Ohhh...you thought
I was mad?

03:28.942 --> 03:31.779
Oh, no, it's just a catchphrase
in our family.

03:31.812 --> 03:33.113
Hey, you jerk.
That kills.

03:33.146 --> 03:35.316
How did you even know
I was gonna do this?

03:35.349 --> 03:36.350
Ow!

03:36.384 --> 03:38.085
Okay, then.

03:38.118 --> 03:41.121
I guess it seems we're not
so in sync on everything.

03:41.154 --> 03:42.490
Are you breaking up
with me?!

03:42.523 --> 03:44.525
No, I'm just seeing
that we have some differences.

03:44.558 --> 03:45.659
No, we don't.

03:45.693 --> 03:47.828
Please. I'm a little
over the top.

03:47.861 --> 03:51.432
I started a 5K run
for my brother.

03:51.465 --> 03:52.900
Are you telling me
you didn't hear

03:52.933 --> 03:54.702
about the thing I started
for JJ?

03:54.735 --> 03:57.538
You started a charity
for your brother, too?

03:57.571 --> 03:58.906
What's it called?

03:58.939 --> 04:00.207
JJ's Dream.

04:00.240 --> 04:01.842
Oh, great name.

04:01.875 --> 04:03.411
It is, right?
[ Chuckles ]

04:03.444 --> 04:05.078
So, we're still in sync.

04:05.112 --> 04:07.281
Just two crazy kids
with special-needs siblings

04:07.315 --> 04:09.683
who they love more than
anything else in this world.

04:09.717 --> 04:13.253
**

04:13.287 --> 04:15.623
[ Whispers ]
I hate you so much right now.

04:19.927 --> 04:21.228
All right, guys, I'm still
a little sore from yesterday,

04:21.261 --> 04:24.798
so I'm gonna need everyone
to pitch in.

04:24.832 --> 04:26.400
[ Indistinct shouting ]
We got a plane to load.

04:26.434 --> 04:28.402
Nothing! Way wide!

04:28.436 --> 04:30.504
Let's go,
Undercover Boss!

04:30.538 --> 04:33.341
I'm not an undercover boss.
This is my real hair.

04:33.374 --> 04:34.742
I want to believe you,
man,

04:34.775 --> 04:36.577
but that is what
an undercover boss would say.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.779
Last hole, Jimmy, all right?
I'm five under!

04:38.812 --> 04:40.348
Wow. All right, um,

04:40.381 --> 04:42.215
finish strong,
meet me on the tarmac.

04:42.249 --> 04:43.216
[ Cheering ]
Booyah!
[ Laughs ]

04:45.085 --> 04:46.354
Hold the plane!

04:46.387 --> 04:50.624
**

04:50.658 --> 04:53.126
We know you have
a choice in carriers!

04:53.160 --> 04:54.928
You chose wrong!

04:54.962 --> 04:55.896
Okay, another leg lift.

04:55.929 --> 04:57.598
Good! Good.

04:57.631 --> 04:58.732
[ Sighs ]

04:58.766 --> 05:00.067
Hi, JJ.

05:00.100 --> 05:02.035
Hey,
JJ's physical therapist.

05:02.069 --> 05:03.737
I've been working with him
for five years.

05:03.771 --> 05:04.938
You should know my name.

05:04.972 --> 05:06.807
Do you know mine?

05:06.840 --> 05:08.141
Well played, JJ's sister.

05:08.175 --> 05:10.811
**

05:10.844 --> 05:11.645
Hey!
Ohh!

05:11.679 --> 05:13.414
What is wrong with you?

05:13.447 --> 05:15.315
This is my space.

05:15.349 --> 05:17.084
Man, I was hiding.

05:17.117 --> 05:18.586
She doesn't know I'm here.

05:18.619 --> 05:20.421
Ever since Joyce and I
almost got together --

05:20.454 --> 05:22.255
"Joyce"!

05:22.289 --> 05:24.558
Hey, Joyce!
Kenneth is in here!

05:24.592 --> 05:25.793
Joyce: I knew it!

05:25.826 --> 05:27.127
**

05:27.160 --> 05:28.729
[ Indistinct shouting ]

05:28.762 --> 05:30.598
So, good news.

05:30.631 --> 05:32.833
Found the bass,
found the dog.

05:34.635 --> 05:36.737
Lost the dog.

05:36.770 --> 05:38.071
Maya! Hi.

05:38.105 --> 05:39.607
[ Cheering ]

05:39.640 --> 05:42.376
Hi, darling. I thought
I'd surprise you with lunch.

05:42.410 --> 05:43.677
Great.
You know the crew.

05:43.711 --> 05:45.012
Oh, yeah.

05:45.045 --> 05:47.748
Undercover Boss, High Waist,
Has-to-Pee.

05:47.781 --> 05:48.549
Darling.

05:50.651 --> 05:52.520
You shouldn't be doing
their work.

05:52.553 --> 05:54.822
You're the boss now.
Command them.

05:54.855 --> 05:56.356
I don't know
how to be the heavy.

05:56.390 --> 05:57.991
Then just be me
being the heavy.

05:58.025 --> 06:01.294
Imagine you're me when
we're in the hospital with JJ.

06:01.328 --> 06:02.696
My son is suffering!

06:02.730 --> 06:05.132
And you're all just
standing around, doing nothing!

06:05.165 --> 06:06.199
He's had his meds.

06:06.233 --> 06:07.701
This isn't about meds!

06:07.735 --> 06:09.002
You gave him applesauce!

06:09.036 --> 06:10.604
He doesn't care for
applesauce!

06:10.638 --> 06:11.872
He needs pudding!

06:11.905 --> 06:14.074
Give my son
his pudding!!

06:16.209 --> 06:17.778
That tone got us
a lot of pudding.

06:17.811 --> 06:19.713
Try it. Go on.

06:19.747 --> 06:22.349
Get that pudding, Jimmy.
Get it.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.051
I said get back to work!

06:24.084 --> 06:27.655
**

06:27.688 --> 06:28.456
Maya: Mm.

06:30.691 --> 06:32.926
I feel like an old man
changing a digital clock.

06:32.960 --> 06:33.994
I can do this!

06:34.027 --> 06:35.395
Hmm!

06:35.429 --> 06:37.698
You make
a rather sexy Maya, too.

06:37.731 --> 06:38.832
Thank you.

06:38.866 --> 06:40.200
Uh, so do you.
Mm.

06:40.233 --> 06:42.503
Dylan:
This is all vegetables.

06:42.536 --> 06:43.904
Where is my meat?

06:45.405 --> 06:46.707
[ Sighs ]

06:49.209 --> 06:50.410
You!

06:50.444 --> 06:51.879
I was saving that!

06:51.912 --> 06:52.946
I'm sorry.

06:52.980 --> 06:54.782
"I'm sorry"
is not going to cut it.

06:54.815 --> 06:56.249
The summer
was so glorious.

06:56.283 --> 06:58.351
We had baseball
and fireflies

06:58.385 --> 07:00.521
and no you!

07:00.554 --> 07:01.855
Now everywhere I turn,
there you ar--

07:01.889 --> 07:03.691
[ Chomps ]

07:03.724 --> 07:06.594
Did you just take
another bite?

07:06.627 --> 07:08.395
You know I stress-eat,
Dylan!

07:09.096 --> 07:11.231
[ Keyboard clacking ]

07:11.264 --> 07:13.667
Hey, can you explain
something?

07:13.701 --> 07:15.869
I keep trying
to search "JJ's Dream,"

07:15.903 --> 07:17.204
but nothing comes up.

07:17.237 --> 07:18.872
No online presence.

07:18.906 --> 07:20.741
That's part
of what sank us.

07:20.774 --> 07:23.276
I've been waiting
for the right time to tell you.

07:23.310 --> 07:25.913
JJ's Dream...

07:25.946 --> 07:26.947
is dead.

07:26.980 --> 07:28.315
But what happened?

07:28.348 --> 07:30.918
It's a tough time
for charities.

07:30.951 --> 07:33.020
You go home tonight,

07:33.053 --> 07:34.622
[ Voice breaking ]
you find that 5K
and you hold it tight,

07:34.655 --> 07:36.089
'cause you just
don't know.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.357
[ Sighs ]

07:37.390 --> 07:39.259
I'm so, so sorry.

07:41.629 --> 07:43.831
Is there anything I can do
to make you feel better?

07:43.864 --> 07:45.365
Some water
would be nice.

07:48.602 --> 07:50.137
"Water"?

07:50.170 --> 07:52.873
Sure. Pretty girl on the bed.
Time for some water!

07:55.008 --> 07:57.377
JJ! I heard
about your dream.

07:58.679 --> 07:59.780
"You did?

07:59.813 --> 08:02.349
It might not
have even been you."

08:04.017 --> 08:06.053
"It was a C-O-M--

08:06.086 --> 08:08.556
composite
of a lot of peop--"

08:08.589 --> 08:09.857
What?

08:09.890 --> 08:12.492
N-- I mean the charity.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

08:12.526 --> 08:14.261
The one Ray started
to honor you.

08:14.294 --> 08:15.428
Such a sweet thing.

08:15.462 --> 08:16.997
Whoa!
Hey, guys.

08:18.498 --> 08:21.101
"So, my C-H-- charity..."

08:21.134 --> 08:23.236
Oh, yeah, I-I was just honest
with Taylor

08:23.270 --> 08:24.972
and how
we're out of money.

08:25.005 --> 08:26.139
Let's just drop it.

08:26.173 --> 08:29.176
"But we'll make money
at the big F-U-N--

08:29.209 --> 08:30.944
fundraiser this Saturday."

08:30.978 --> 08:32.012
Oh!
There's a fundraiser?

08:32.045 --> 08:33.513
No,
there's no fundraiser.

08:33.547 --> 08:37.017
"Yes. At the A-S-H--
Ashcroft.

08:37.050 --> 08:38.919
You must come."

08:38.952 --> 08:40.020
I wouldn't miss it!

08:40.053 --> 08:42.289
The fundraiser
was canceled, remember?

08:42.322 --> 08:45.092
"P-A-- Pamela e-mailed.

08:45.125 --> 08:46.627
It's back on."

08:46.660 --> 08:49.262
That's impossible!
Pamela's dead!

08:49.296 --> 08:52.666
"Not Pamela A.
Pamela G."

08:52.700 --> 08:53.867
Well, this is great!

08:53.901 --> 08:56.069
I don't know.
She just died.

08:56.103 --> 08:57.671
"We'll do it for Pamela.

08:57.705 --> 08:59.673
And you.

08:59.707 --> 09:02.943
You W-O--
You worked so hard.

09:02.976 --> 09:06.446
You're going to get
what you D-E-- deserve."

09:07.547 --> 09:09.249
Oh, I'm so excited!

09:11.284 --> 09:12.452
Here's your water.

09:17.390 --> 09:20.761
[ Screams ]
[ Screams ]

09:20.794 --> 09:22.529
I was trying
not to startle you!

09:22.562 --> 09:23.831
What better place
would you stand

09:23.864 --> 09:25.866
if you were trying
to startle me?!

09:25.899 --> 09:27.668
Listen, I thought about
what you had to say

09:27.701 --> 09:30.671
about me being in your space,
and I get it.

09:30.704 --> 09:34.074
When I was a kid,
I had to share a room
with my two sisters.

09:34.107 --> 09:35.508
That was bad enough.

09:35.542 --> 09:37.044
And then she came --

09:37.077 --> 09:38.879
Aunt Martha.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.548
Every time I turned around,
she was in my face!

09:41.581 --> 09:43.550
I couldn't escape
that woman.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.686
A few years in...
she died.

09:45.719 --> 09:46.854
And you felt terrible?

09:46.887 --> 09:48.822
[ Laughs ] It was
the best day of my life!

09:48.856 --> 09:50.924
The woman was horrible.

09:50.958 --> 09:54.094
My point is, I will not be
your Aunt Martha.

09:54.127 --> 09:56.897
From now on, you'll never see me
in this house again -- ever.

09:56.930 --> 09:59.432
This house is way too small.
It would be impos--

10:01.234 --> 10:03.270
Dang!

10:03.303 --> 10:05.639
Undercover Boss,
back to work.

10:05.673 --> 10:07.340
Oh, yeah, yeah.
In a bit, Jimmy.

10:07.374 --> 10:09.242
Now. You can play luggage golf
on your break.

10:09.276 --> 10:10.744
But I'm on
a hot streak here.

10:10.778 --> 10:12.212
Hey, actually, you know what --
can you film this?

10:14.247 --> 10:17.350
No, I've tried doing
my best "Maya." He's immune.

10:17.384 --> 10:19.319
No, no. J-Just tell him more
forcefully to go back to work.

10:21.889 --> 10:23.023
Hey!

10:23.056 --> 10:24.224
I'm talking to you!

10:24.257 --> 10:25.625
What's with you, Jimmy?

10:25.659 --> 10:27.627
Oh, see?
You've got his attention. Go on.

10:27.661 --> 10:29.730
Put the bag down now.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.564
Ooh, that was very Maya,
wasn't it?

10:31.598 --> 10:33.200
It was also very hot.

10:33.233 --> 10:34.501
Or what?

10:34.534 --> 10:35.903
Do you want to find out?

10:35.936 --> 10:37.037
That's it, baby.

10:37.070 --> 10:38.438
Yeah, be me for Mommy.

10:43.010 --> 10:43.777
Nice shot.

10:43.811 --> 10:45.612
You're fired.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.614
Yeah, that's right!
Who else wants some?

10:47.647 --> 10:49.116
I do! I do! Me! Me!
Get home quickly!

10:52.185 --> 10:53.120
So, this is
the Balboa Room.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.254
It's our most popular
event space.

10:54.287 --> 10:57.958
Is this kind of
what you had in mind?

10:57.991 --> 11:01.729
You know, Marci, today I'm just
exploring the possibilities,

11:01.762 --> 11:03.463
getting the juices
flowing.

11:03.496 --> 11:04.932
Okay.
Uh, when is the event?

11:04.965 --> 11:06.099
[ Shakily ]
It's tomorrow.

11:06.133 --> 11:07.500
Oh. My.

11:07.534 --> 11:10.337
Um...well, the room
is available tomorrow.

11:10.370 --> 11:11.905
Feels meant to be.
[ Chuckles ]

11:11.939 --> 11:14.674
Now, I see
that the space is empty.

11:14.708 --> 11:18.345
I'm guessing the hotel provides
tables, chairs...

11:18.378 --> 11:19.780
guests?

11:19.813 --> 11:21.949
Well, traditionally,
the host provides the guests.

11:21.982 --> 11:23.650
[ Scoffs ]
I'm not fancy like that.

11:23.683 --> 11:24.952
[ Both laugh ]

11:24.985 --> 11:26.619
All right,
now let's talk cost.

11:26.653 --> 11:28.688
Of course.
This is our proposal.

11:28.722 --> 11:30.157
Oh, it's in its own folder.
[ Chuckles ]

11:30.190 --> 11:31.024
Yes.

11:32.893 --> 11:35.262
You know, I was hoping
that the fact

11:35.295 --> 11:38.198
that it's for a charity
might factor into the cost.

11:38.231 --> 11:40.868
JJ's Dream does
some very important work.

11:40.901 --> 11:43.136
What exactly is it
that you do?

11:43.170 --> 11:44.972
What might you...
like us to do?

11:46.206 --> 11:47.307
Can I have
the folder back?

11:47.340 --> 11:49.342
Yes, you can.
[ Sighs ]

11:49.376 --> 11:55.816
Kenneth:
"I W-A-- want some chips."

11:55.849 --> 11:57.050
Sure thing.

11:57.084 --> 11:58.485
Gotcha!

11:58.518 --> 12:00.353
Oh.

12:00.387 --> 12:01.855
Okay, big man.

12:01.889 --> 12:05.525
I guess there's nothing I can do
to lure you out.

12:05.558 --> 12:07.194
Jazz is lame!

12:07.227 --> 12:09.797
Hot tubs are lame!

12:09.830 --> 12:11.264
That's all I know
about you!

12:11.298 --> 12:15.168
**

12:15.202 --> 12:17.204
I've been
a very bad employee.

12:17.237 --> 12:20.573
I've been late,
I've stolen office supplies,

12:20.607 --> 12:23.210
I microwaved fish
in the break room.

12:23.243 --> 12:27.714
**

12:27.747 --> 12:28.715
Please stop.

12:28.748 --> 12:29.917
Why?

12:29.950 --> 12:31.351
I'm tired,
had an awful day,

12:31.384 --> 12:33.686
and Kenneth is very clearly
standing in our closet.

12:33.720 --> 12:35.755
Oop! Sorry.

12:35.789 --> 12:37.324
I was just hiding
from Dylan.

12:37.357 --> 12:39.426
I didn't see
any sexy role play.

12:39.459 --> 12:41.561
[ Trills, chuckles ]

12:41.594 --> 12:42.595
[ Door opens ]

12:42.629 --> 12:44.731
Work was a nightmare.

12:44.764 --> 12:47.267
We got so much done.

12:47.300 --> 12:49.436
Everyone's doing their jobs,
but they're all afraid of me.

12:49.469 --> 12:50.838
Where's the fun in that?

12:50.871 --> 12:52.572
Well, you're the boss.
It's not supposed to be fun.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.074
It can be a little fun.

12:54.107 --> 12:56.009
It's not
my dream career.

12:56.043 --> 12:58.278
The nicknames, the games --
that's all for me.

12:58.311 --> 13:00.513
You know another airline
scooped up Undercover Boss?

13:00.547 --> 13:01.949
Oh, no.
I didn't watch the news today.

13:01.982 --> 13:04.417
I tried to be you.

13:04.451 --> 13:05.518
I'm not you.

13:05.552 --> 13:06.686
Then you've got to try
and find a way

13:06.719 --> 13:08.655
to be the boss and be you.

13:08.688 --> 13:11.724
Such a shame, though.

13:11.758 --> 13:13.827
Stern Jimmy
really worked for me.

13:13.861 --> 13:16.196
Like, really.

13:16.229 --> 13:18.598
Oh, sorry.
[ Sighs ]

13:18.631 --> 13:20.800
It was nice being the kind
of boss that turns you on,

13:20.834 --> 13:25.372
but...I need to be the kind
of boss that turns me on.

13:25.405 --> 13:33.113
**

13:33.146 --> 13:40.553
**

13:40.587 --> 13:41.554
[ Sniffs ]

13:41.588 --> 13:44.391
Is that a gas leak?

13:44.424 --> 13:45.358
A gas leak!

13:46.960 --> 13:50.563
So, this fake JJ's Dream
was supposed to do what?

13:50.597 --> 13:51.831
I came up with it
last night.

13:51.865 --> 13:53.733
JJ's Dream builds
accessible playgrounds

13:53.766 --> 13:55.768
where kids of all abilities
can play together.

13:55.802 --> 13:56.769
Kind of nice, right?

13:56.803 --> 13:58.671
"She'd love you for that.

13:58.705 --> 13:59.907
Pass."

13:59.940 --> 14:02.109
Oh, JJ,
isn't it a lovely thing

14:02.142 --> 14:04.011
your liar brother
isn't doing?

14:04.044 --> 14:06.613
It doesn't matter.
I don't have to really do it.

14:06.646 --> 14:08.748
The gas leak in the kitchen
gave me an idea.

14:08.781 --> 14:10.783
Taylor and I will
get to the hotel,

14:10.817 --> 14:12.953
I'll get a text on my phone
saying that there's a gas leak

14:12.986 --> 14:14.587
and that
the fundraiser's off.

14:14.621 --> 14:16.689
All you guys have to do
is show up and act disappointed.

14:16.723 --> 14:19.659
Well, we won't have to act
disappointed, darling.

14:19.692 --> 14:22.229
Now we're all getting dragged
into your latest moonwalk.

14:22.262 --> 14:23.997
You lied.
Deal with it.

14:24.031 --> 14:25.665
We all lie.

14:25.698 --> 14:28.001
Our family crest is
Pinocchio pushing a wheelchair.

14:28.035 --> 14:30.237
Wait. There's a gas leak
in our kitchen?

14:30.270 --> 14:32.205
JJ, I was wrong to use you
to score points with Taylor.

14:32.239 --> 14:33.340
I'm sorry.

14:33.373 --> 14:36.043
But making me do
this fundraiser --

14:36.076 --> 14:37.544
what do you get
out of this?

14:37.577 --> 14:39.279
"This."

14:39.312 --> 14:42.149
So that's it?
No one's gonna help me?

14:42.182 --> 14:44.651
When JJ's in trouble, you guys
do anything to help him.

14:44.684 --> 14:46.086
Mom,
you've got a phone tree

14:46.119 --> 14:47.720
full of strangers
who you'd kill for,

14:47.754 --> 14:49.589
but you won't do
this one thing for me!

14:49.622 --> 14:51.091
Ray, wait.

14:51.124 --> 14:53.493
And this is
a perfectly acceptable moonwalk.

14:53.526 --> 15:03.070
**

15:03.103 --> 15:06.239
Okay, this might be
the gas leak talking,

15:06.273 --> 15:09.242
but I think his moonwalk's
gotten pretty sharp.

15:14.481 --> 15:16.583
It's no fun
to watch Ray suffer,

15:16.616 --> 15:19.352
but he did
bring it on himself.

15:19.386 --> 15:23.190
Jimmy: "No. I B-R--
brought it on him."

15:23.223 --> 15:25.225
So what?
You're a big brother.

15:25.258 --> 15:26.893
Big brothers make
little brothers pay.

15:28.928 --> 15:32.732
"They also H-E--
help sometimes.

15:32.765 --> 15:36.403
Maybe it's time
Ray gets a W-I--"

15:36.436 --> 15:39.106
Oh, win --
"Ray gets a win."

15:39.139 --> 15:40.773
Ray gets a win.

15:40.807 --> 15:42.642
All: [ Chanting ]
Ray gets a win.

15:42.675 --> 15:45.778
Ray gets a win.
Yeah. He'll fail
on his own terms.

15:45.812 --> 15:47.447
He'll fail
on his own terms!

15:47.480 --> 15:49.216
He'll fail
on his own terms!

15:49.249 --> 15:50.450
He'll fail
on his own terms!

15:51.884 --> 15:53.753
Excuse me.

15:53.786 --> 15:55.422
I'm here
for Undercover Boss.

15:55.455 --> 15:57.590
Who?
Oh, sorry. Uh, Joe?

15:57.624 --> 15:59.226
Medium height,
fake-looking goatee?

15:59.259 --> 16:00.460
You mean '80s Magician?

16:00.493 --> 16:02.095
Oh, my God. He does look like
an '80s magician.

16:02.129 --> 16:03.396
He really does.

16:03.430 --> 16:04.597
Doesn't matter.
I'm hiring him back.

16:04.631 --> 16:07.234
No way. He adds character
to my crew.

16:07.267 --> 16:08.468
I-I'll play you for him.

16:08.501 --> 16:10.203
What?
One round of luggage golf.

16:10.237 --> 16:11.738
I win, I get him back.

16:11.771 --> 16:12.972
And if I win?

16:13.006 --> 16:15.608
Then you can have
any member of my crew.

16:15.642 --> 16:16.809
Long Hair Bald,

16:16.843 --> 16:17.844
Too Handsome,

16:17.877 --> 16:19.879
Old Pregnant.

16:19.912 --> 16:23.350
**

16:23.383 --> 16:26.619
* You're the best around

16:26.653 --> 16:28.421
* Nothing's gonna ever
keep you down *

16:28.455 --> 16:31.624
* You're the best around

16:31.658 --> 16:34.294
* Nothing's gonna ever
keep you down *

16:34.327 --> 16:37.430
Give it up, Jimmy. You need
to sink this to win.

16:37.464 --> 16:39.899
[ Whispers ]
It ain't happening.

16:39.932 --> 16:41.501
I think you underestimate
how much I screwed around

16:41.534 --> 16:43.170
before I was in charge.

16:43.203 --> 16:50.177
**

16:50.210 --> 16:53.180
* You're the best around

16:53.213 --> 16:54.914
That's my boss!

16:54.947 --> 16:56.616
What's going on here?

16:56.649 --> 16:59.619
I just won you back
in a high-stakes game
of luggage golf.

16:59.652 --> 17:00.653
You're working for me
again.

17:00.687 --> 17:01.988
Wait, you won me?

17:02.021 --> 17:04.023
What, like a --
some kind of carnival prize?

17:06.993 --> 17:09.162
Call me a rock-hard Minion
full of sawdust,

17:09.196 --> 17:11.030
because I am yours.

17:11.064 --> 17:12.532
[ Laughter ]

17:12.565 --> 17:14.033
Boss move, Jimmy!

17:14.067 --> 17:15.468
You'd know.

17:15.502 --> 17:17.537
Okay, and reach.

17:17.570 --> 17:19.406
Reach. Get those toes.
You got this.

17:19.439 --> 17:20.173
[ Screams ]

17:20.207 --> 17:21.574
[ Screams ]

17:21.608 --> 17:22.442
Oh.

17:22.475 --> 17:25.312
Huh. I'm a coward.

17:25.345 --> 17:26.879
You're not safe with me.

17:26.913 --> 17:28.981
Sorry, Joyce.
I-I thought you were Kenneth.

17:29.015 --> 17:31.050
Where is he?

17:31.084 --> 17:34.020
"He went home."

17:34.053 --> 17:36.055
Aww. Already?

17:36.089 --> 17:38.291
"You miss him."

17:38.325 --> 17:40.793
Huh.
I guess I kind of do.

17:40.827 --> 17:43.029
Yeah.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.331
Let's torch his car.

17:47.134 --> 17:50.270
Ray, are you okay?
You look really nervous.

17:50.303 --> 17:52.839
Yeah, it's just
normal pre-gala jitters.

17:52.872 --> 17:54.006
The day
I don't get these,

17:54.040 --> 17:56.576
I'll know it's time
to get out of the gala game.

17:56.609 --> 17:58.478
Hold on.
I'm getting a text.

17:58.511 --> 17:59.912
I hope
it's not bad news.

18:01.314 --> 18:02.949
Oh, no!
There's been a gas le--

18:02.982 --> 18:04.851
Ray,
it's your parents!

18:04.884 --> 18:07.520
Mom. Dad. You're here.

18:07.554 --> 18:08.621
You must've heard
about the gas --

18:08.655 --> 18:10.557
Taylor,
don't you look lovely.

18:10.590 --> 18:12.091
Darling,
we're so proud of you.

18:12.125 --> 18:14.026
Tonight's
gonna be awesome.

18:14.060 --> 18:15.695
Wait! No! The gas leak!

18:15.728 --> 18:16.996
It's gonna blow!

18:17.029 --> 18:19.566
[ Big-band music plays ]

18:19.599 --> 18:23.536
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:23.570 --> 18:24.737
This is amazing, Ray!

18:24.771 --> 18:25.905
[ Thud ]

18:25.938 --> 18:26.739
Ray?

18:28.040 --> 18:29.709
Ooh. Ohh.
Are you okay?

18:29.742 --> 18:32.179
Sorry.
Didn't faint. Slipped.

18:32.212 --> 18:33.413
I'm gonna go check it out.

18:33.446 --> 18:35.915
[ Music continues ]

18:35.948 --> 18:38.050
Ray: What happened?
What is this all?

18:38.084 --> 18:40.052
Your brother thought
you deserved a win.

18:40.086 --> 18:41.654
So your mother
sent a flare

18:41.688 --> 18:43.623
up the special-needs-mom
phone tree.

18:43.656 --> 18:45.358
Greer has a hookup
at the hotel.

18:45.392 --> 18:48.094
Helen has a catering company,
so there's food.

18:48.127 --> 18:49.229
But just for Taylor.

18:49.262 --> 18:51.198
But...all the people?

18:51.231 --> 18:54.367
Oh, Danica --
she runs 12-step programs.

18:54.401 --> 18:57.103
Each table
is a different addiction.

18:57.136 --> 18:59.806
Ah, but tonight, they're all
addicted to helping you.

18:59.839 --> 19:01.741
And also still drugs.

19:01.774 --> 19:05.312
**

19:05.345 --> 19:08.315
[ Laughs ]

19:08.348 --> 19:11.384
So -- I only hide from you
when we're at home.

19:11.418 --> 19:13.320
So, how does
such a pretty girl

19:13.353 --> 19:16.256
get addicted
to such an ugly thing?

19:16.289 --> 19:19.459
Fine. Act like
I'm not even here.

19:19.492 --> 19:20.460
Isn't that what you want?

19:20.493 --> 19:21.994
You're not Aunt Martha.

19:22.028 --> 19:23.263
I don't want you dead.

19:23.296 --> 19:24.797
That's...

19:24.831 --> 19:27.166
the nicest thing
you've ever said to me.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.236
I didn't realize
how fun you are.

19:29.269 --> 19:30.437
Come back.

19:30.470 --> 19:32.305
I will.

19:32.339 --> 19:35.007
But I need
to ask you something first.

19:35.041 --> 19:37.710
Where the hell am I,
what is JJ's Dream, and...

19:37.744 --> 19:39.679
can a brother
get some food?!

19:39.712 --> 19:43.149
Attention, everyone.
The big moment has arrived.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.452
It's now time to present

19:45.485 --> 19:49.356
the JJ's Dream "Dreamer
of the Year Award" to...

19:49.389 --> 19:50.457
Ray DiMeo!

19:50.490 --> 19:52.959
[ Applause ]

19:52.992 --> 19:53.660
Whoo!

19:55.662 --> 19:56.963
I had to swipe this
from reception,

19:56.996 --> 19:59.098
but congrats
on being such a great hotel.

20:03.035 --> 20:05.372
[ Clears throat ] Wow.
I-I don't know what to say.

20:05.405 --> 20:07.740
I'd like to thank Taylor.

20:07.774 --> 20:10.477
I'd also like to thank
my family.

20:10.510 --> 20:11.811
Taylor's my girlfriend.

20:11.844 --> 20:14.046
[ Clears throat ]

20:14.080 --> 20:16.816
Mom, Dad, Dylan, JJ,

20:16.849 --> 20:19.986
you had my back
when I needed you.

20:20.019 --> 20:21.621
You've done so much,
I feel kind of bad.

20:24.023 --> 20:26.359
Wait. I know
what I'm gonna do.

20:26.393 --> 20:28.227
I'm doing this charity!

20:28.261 --> 20:29.629
Like, for real.

20:29.662 --> 20:31.664
JJ's Dream is a reality.

20:31.698 --> 20:33.132
We're doing this.

20:33.165 --> 20:34.967
Thank you, everyone.
Good night.

20:35.001 --> 20:37.537
[ Applause ]

20:37.570 --> 20:40.373
I'm so proud of you.

20:40.407 --> 20:41.941
I just have
one question.

20:41.974 --> 20:43.976
Up there,
you said you were doing it.

20:44.010 --> 20:46.813
But what exactly
does JJ's Dream do?

20:52.184 --> 20:54.387
"It B-U-I-- builds

20:54.421 --> 20:56.523
P-L-- playgrounds

20:56.556 --> 21:01.027
so kids of all
A-B-I-- abilities

21:01.060 --> 21:05.231
can play T-O-- together."

21:05.264 --> 21:06.533
[ Gasps ]

21:06.566 --> 21:08.868
That is
such a beautiful idea.

21:08.901 --> 21:11.971
[ Whispers ] I love you
so much right now.

21:12.004 --> 21:15.408
**

21:15.442 --> 21:16.909
Owwwww!

21:16.943 --> 21:20.547
**

21:20.580 --> 21:21.948
[ Sighs ]

21:21.981 --> 21:28.187
**

21:28.220 --> 21:29.221
Man, he's good.
